data.title: Chetan Chandra
data.text:
Indian actor

Chetan Chandra (born 10 April 1986) is an Indian actor working in the Kannada film industry.[1]

Early life and family

[edit]

Chetan Chandra was born to K. B. Ramachandra and B. N. Anusuya. K. B. Ramachandra is a mining engineer in Malaysia. Chandra is a graduate in Information Science Engineering. He is married to Rachana Hegade.[2] He has a brother, Nitin Chandra.[2]

Career

[edit]

He made his acting debut in the 2008 released film, PUC alongside Harshika Poonacha, but was more noticed for the film Premism (2010).[citation needed] For the film Kumbha Rashi, he underwent a rigorous workout to develop eight pack abs.[2]

He has signed Nindru Kolvaan,[citation needed] a Tamil film directed by V. P. Shankar.
